{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid, weigh in rice, lentils, 300 g water and set aside to soak.","Place onions, garlic and olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and sauté <nobr>3 min\/120°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add crushed tomatoes, remaining 800 g water, vinegar, stock paste, cumin, chili flakes, salt, pepper and mix with spatula.","Drain rice and lentils through simmering basket and insert simmering basket carefully to avoid spilling tomato sauce. Mix well with spatula and cook <nobr>16 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add pasta and chick peas to simmering basket. Mix with spatula and cook <nobr>13 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer rice mixture into a deep serving bowl, pour over some tomato sauce and mix gently with a fork.","Pour remaining tomato sauce into a jug and serve with Koshari stew. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["130 g basmati rice","60 g red lentils","1100 g water","100 g onions, cut into quarters","4 garlic cloves","20 g olive oil","400 g canned crushed tomatoes","1 tbsp vinegar","1 heaped tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","½ tsp ground cumin","½ tsp dried chilli flakes, adjust to taste","1 tsp salt, adjust to taste","1 pinch freshly ground black pepper","80 g short dried pasta (e.g. elbow macaroni)","50 g cooked chickpeas, rinsed (weight after draining) (optional)"]}],"id":"r168155","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-EgKooJ_artc\/XZMx5s3wNXI\/AAAAAAAAaeM\/8miF6qTCidIrSVYjDOoJ4tmGoK3h18epQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_-CRXUOK7vGgcd-0G.png","title":"Koshari stew","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.1 g","fat":"6.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"55.1 g","calories":"1330 kJ \/ 318 kcal"},"usefulItems":"deep bowl, jug","hintsAndTricks":["If sauce needs thickening, at the end of <nobr>step 6<\/nobr> reduce by steaming further <strong><nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr><\/strong> without measuring cup and place simmering basket onto the mixing bowl lid to prevent splashing.","Serve Koshari stew with finely sliced deep fried onions on top."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","45m","4 portions"]}